Personal Projects

Gym Automation Project

The inspiration for this project was to reduce how much time I spent planning out what workouts I had to do and for how many sets, reps, etc. So, following the fundamentals of Renaissance Periodization, I built a progressive gym routine automator that gives you workouts that are progressive, and are based on aggregating your recent soreness levels per muscle.

Valorant Role Predictor

I've been playing Valorant, a tactical first-person-shooter developed by Riot Games since 2020. I was curious to explore whether the ability icons assoicated with each agents' abilities have any correlation to the role they play. I used a convolutional neural network with pooling to investigate this.

Recoup

An app that utilizes the OpenAI API that was built during a hackathon in the span of 10 hours. The app was able to (using custom prompts to GPT), provide instructions on how to recycle, reuse, or compost any item that it was queried about. If the project was taken further, we would have incorporated a points system (such as a video game), and utilize location-based APIs to provide the user with local composting centers.

Anomaly Detection

Current work-in-progress project highlighting my skills in data generation, and anomaly detection utilizing isolation forests from Scikit.

Smart Calendar

The motivation for this work-in-progress project came from the fact that I spend around 2-3 hours a week sorting through my calendar to find the optimal timing for my events and tasks given my constraints. Currently, it has the capability to satisfy a set of constraints using arc and node consistency, but is still extremely limited. The ultimate goal for this project is to be fully automated after having learned your constraints, and would simply need any new events, or tasks and deadlines you may have as an input. I also plan to utilize a neural network to learn the habits of the user over time, but this will be a more long term goal.

About me

My name is Vivek, but I go by viv. I was born and raised in Hong Kong, and major in Computer Science, while minoring in Data Science at Loyola Marymount University, where I will graduate from in Spring 2025. My main interest in Computer Science is Artificial Intelligence, especially in conjunction with Data. I believe that 90% of the menial tasks humans do on a daily basis can eventually be automated, and can therefore free up humans to do creative thinking, which is what we're best at.

My long term goal is to spearhead this development by working towards a PhD within a subfield of AI, but for now I'm working on a variety of projects to develop my own skills and display my capabilities to the world.
